cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.AI

This paper deals with natural language processing and information retrieval techniques to extract semantic relatedness between cities from news articles. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning and data mining techniques, which are commonly used in sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a computational framework, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
